      <section eId="sec_CCP-3371">
        <num>CCP 3371</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3371__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>At any time after the homologation of the final tableau of distribution, a legatee or an heir may file a petition to be sent into possession, alleging the facts showing that he is a legatee or an heir. Â Upon the filing of such a petition, the court shall order the executor to show cause why the petitioner should not be sent into possession.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3371__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Evidence of the allegations in the petition for possession showing that the petitioner is a legatee or an heir shall be submitted to the court as provided by Articles 2821 through 2823.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111731</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
